>Rob_Robinsky: AEKMNNP K10 KAN.E +25 363
#note MAK here sets up a couple of crazy wins by creating bingos in two spots: a T? draw leads to INPAT(I)EN(T) on row 2, while a U? draw leads to NENUPHAR on row 1 (and UNPANEL on column O to make NENUPHAR unblockable). However, the best try here is really cool and unusual - KNAP at 10K wins with draws of A? or E? by setting up big outs in two spots! see if you can work through the pre-endgames.
>JD: ?AENOTU O1 .ANOTUbE +74 443
